  "prompt": "Can you privately change your legal name so that it will not be public record?",
  "response": "In the United States, legal name changes typically require a court process, which often results in the new name being a matter of public record. However, some states offer alternative options, such as confidentiality programs or name changes for specific populations (like survivors of domestic violence), which may allow for certain protections to keep the new name private.\n\nIf you're considering a name change and want to keep it private, it's essential to research the laws in your specific state or consult with a legal professional who can provide guidance based on your circumstances. They can help you understand your options and any available confidentiality protections.",
